abstract: Senator Elizabeth Warren was among several Democratic presidential candidates voicing support for the strike in the country’s third-largest school district.
snippet: Senator Elizabeth Warren was among several Democratic presidential candidates voicing support for the strike in the country’s third-largest school district.
lead_paragraph: CHICAGO — Senator Elizabeth Warren waded into the crowd outside a Chicago elementary school on Tuesday morning, offering hugs and handshakes and words of support for more than 20,000 teachers whose strike had canceled classes for four days in the country’s third-largest school district.

abstract: Stormy news cycles, and an audience thirsty for political commentary, have changed what works on TV at 11:35 p.m.
snippet: Stormy news cycles, and an audience thirsty for political commentary, have changed what works on TV at 11:35 p.m.
lead_paragraph: The formula for success on the big late-night network television shows used to be simple. Keep it light, keep it moving and book a major star, preferably one in the news.

headline_print_headline: As News Drives Late Night, Anchors Join A-List

abstract: Ms. Ocasio-Cortez hailed Mr. Sanders and his influence on Democratic Party politics at Mr. Sanders’s first rally since his heart attack two weeks ago.
snippet: Ms. Ocasio-Cortez hailed Mr. Sanders and his influence on Democratic Party politics at Mr. Sanders’s first rally since his heart attack two weeks ago.
lead_paragraph: Senator Bernie Sanders wanted a show of force to convince voters he was back from his heart attack, and he produced one on Saturday: At his first rally since the episode just two and a half weeks ago, he reveled in one of the most coveted endorsements in the Democratic Party, from Representative Alexandria Ocasio-Cortez of New York.

abstract: Here’s a rundown of major things that happened in the presidential campaign this week.
snippet: Here’s a rundown of major things that happened in the presidential campaign this week.
lead_paragraph: We here on The New York Times Politics desk had a busy and exciting week helping to host the fourth Democratic debate. Tuesday night was especially frenetic, with the debate, third-quarter fund-raising reports and a pair of major endorsements all in the news.

abstract: In the past three months, Mr. Biden spent more on his campaign than he raised. He begins an aggressive phase of the primary race with far less cash on hand than top rivals.
snippet: In the past three months, Mr. Biden spent more on his campaign than he raised. He begins an aggressive phase of the primary race with far less cash on hand than top rivals.
lead_paragraph: WESTERVILLE, Ohio — Former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s campaign began October with less than $9 million in the bank as the 2020 Democratic primary race entered a new and more aggressive phase, barely more than a third as much cash as that of his leading rival, Senator Elizabeth Warren, and nearly $25 million behind the race’s money leader, Senator Bernie Sanders.

abstract: We asked veterans of political debates for their reviews of each of the Democratic hopefuls onstage Tuesday.
snippet: We asked veterans of political debates for their reviews of each of the Democratic hopefuls onstage Tuesday.
lead_paragraph: Before Tuesday’s Democratic primary debate, we asked political debate coaches and experts to tell us what each candidate needed to do to have a good night. Here’s that story. Today, we asked the experts how the candidates did.
